{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"InputDeviceInfo","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.InputDeviceInfo"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li class=\"section\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Media_Capture_and_Streams_API\">Media Capture and Streams API</a></li><li class=\"section\"><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>InputDeviceInfo</code></a></em></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo/getCapabilities\"><code>getCapabilities()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\"><code>MediaDeviceInfo</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Media Capture and Streams</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack\"><code>CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLCanvasElement/captureStream\"><code>HTMLCanvasElement.captureStream()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLMediaElement/captureStream\"><code>HTMLMediaElement.captureStream()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\"><code>MediaDeviceInfo</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices\"><code>MediaDevices</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStream\"><code>MediaStream</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrack\"><code>MediaStreamTrack</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrackEvent\"><code>MediaStreamTrackEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackConstraints\"><code>MediaTrackConstraints</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackSettings\"><code>MediaTrackSettings</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackSupportedConstraints\"><code>MediaTrackSupportedConstraints</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/mediaDevices\"><code>Navigator.mediaDevices</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OverconstrainedError\"><code>OverconstrainedError</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>InputDeviceInfo</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Media_Capture_and_Streams_API\">Media Capture and Streams API</a> gives access to the capabilities of the input device that it represents.</p>\n<p><code>InputDeviceInfo</code> objects are returned by <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices/enumerateDevices\"><code>MediaDevices.enumerateDevices()</code></a> if the returned device is an audio or video input device.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"120\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"60\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      MediaDeviceInfo\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"120\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"150\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"120,14 130,9 130,19 120,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"150\" y=\"0\" width=\"120\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"210\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      InputDeviceInfo\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>Also inherits properties from its parent interface, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\"><code>MediaDeviceInfo</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>Also inherits methods from its parent interface, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\"><code>MediaDeviceInfo</code></a>.</em></p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"inputdeviceinfo.getcapabilities\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo/getCapabilities\"><code>InputDeviceInfo.getCapabilities()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a <code>MediaTrackCapabilities</code> object describing the primary audio or video track of a device's <code>MediaStream</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following example gets all media devices with <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices/enumerateDevices\"><code>MediaDevices.enumerateDevices()</code></a>. If any of the devices are input devices then <code>console.log(device)</code> will print an <code>InputDeviceInfo</code> object to the console.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></div><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator.mediaDevices.enumerateDevices().then((devices) =&gt; {\n  devices.forEach((device) =&gt; {\n    console.log(device); // an InputDeviceInfo object if the device is an input device, otherwise a MediaDeviceInfo object.\n  });\n});\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-inputdeviceinfo","title":"Media Capture and Streams"}],"query":"api.InputDeviceInfo"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.InputDeviceInfo"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The InputDeviceInfo interface of the Media Capture and Streams API gives access to the capabilities of the input device that it represents.","popularity":0.0019,"modified":null,"other_translations":[],"pageType":"web-api-interface","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/inputdeviceinfo","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/inputdeviceinfo/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"InputDeviceInfo","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo","title":"InputDeviceInfo"}],"pageTitle":"InputDeviceInfo - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false},"url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo"}